<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-17T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="940" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d940">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00 Revolutions/347: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-17T12:00:00-05:00">July 17,
                                    1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>109. My telegram No. 105 and 107. Fighting vicinity <persName corresp="#p_TMGRL1">Trujillo</persName> has terminated but scattered
                            rebel bands operating mountains east of <persName corresp="#p_TMGRL1">Trujillo</persName>. Court martial functioning with a number of
                            summary executions. Imposing funeral of officers killed <persName corresp="#p_TMGRL1">Trujillo</persName> held at Lima yesterday used
                            as demonstration of strength Government and for political effect.</p>
                        <p>Strong undercurrent discontent prevalent in Lima and throughout country
                            and wholesale arrests being made. All press despatches, including
                            Associated Press and United Press are dictated by Government and
                            Department should place no reliance in their accuracy.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>